  "schema:version": "1",
  "schema:description": "This raster shows a large portion of Lake Opinicon’s bathymetry and can be used in studies requiring precise depths of the lake. The raster has a cell size of 3 and 3 meters and was created using the Hydroball medium-shallow model. The points were then interpolated into a raster in ArcMap using Natural Neighbor (Spatial Analyst). This file could be accessed by using the free software QGIS.",
